narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Russ 130 is a good review of basic Russian but also pushes into more complex topics. I'd definitely recommend it, especially if Irina is teaching it again.

Russian 130 is a great L3 class, especially for students who place into it as freshmen. The class moves at an excellent pace and I would say that I learned more Russian in this one semester than I did in two years of high school. The homework is also very doable and does not add too much stress to your daily life.
It's a class for intermediate Russian students looking to improve upon the basics. If a student wants to improve in Russian, I absolutely recommend the class.
I really love the Russian program here at Yale. I enjoy going to class, which for me is a very odd sentiment. Take a Russian language class while at Yale - you won't regret it.
I would recommend Russian 130 1 to another student, but it is a lot of daily work.
